@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Introduction@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   CreateAminetReadMe is a program to create Aminet ReadMe's. It has many
   nice features:
   @{B}*@{UB} MUI interface. (Using MUIRexx!)
   @{B}*@{UB} It's small.
   @{B}*@{UB} It's very easy to use.
   @{B}*@{UB} It can load EVERY ReadMe, not just the ones created by CAR!

   Why did I do it?
   Well, it's the most common reason... I've tried some other Aminet ReadMe
   Creators but they really SUCK... (Sorry for this but I think so!)
   So I started on this and my goal is to make the best one there is, I'm not
   far away from that goal now...
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Disclaimer" "Disclaimer"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Disclaimer@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   You are using this program at your own risk. I'm NOT responsible for
   anything this program might do. (@{B}Although it shouldn't do any damage!@{UB})
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Copyright" "Copyright"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Copyright@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   CreateAminetReadMe is ©Copyright Lorens Johansson 1998-1999.
   This program is E-Mailware... If you use it then please send me an E-Mail
   so I can see how many people who uses this program... That's all I ask.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Requirements" "Requirements"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}Requirements@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   · AmigaOS 2.0+ (Since ARexx was introduced in 2.0)
   · You must have MUIRexx installed and a MUIRexx assign to it.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "How to install"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}How to install@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   Copy the drawer wherever you want.
   Be sure that you have MUIRexx: assigned to where MUIRexx is.
   That's it!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "HowTo" "How to use"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}How to use@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   Please E-Mail me if you have any trouble with this program, and I'll
   do my best to help you!

@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
                              T H E   M E N U
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
    @{B}* CreateAminetReadMe@{UB}
      @{U}MUI Prefs...@{UU}
         Brings up the MUI preferences.
      @{U}Save Prefs@{UU}
         Saves the preferences.
      @{U}About MUI:@{UU}
         Shows the About MUI requester.
      @{U}About:@{UU}
         Shows some info about the program.
      @{U}Quit:@{UU}
         Quits the program.

@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
                               T H E   G U I
@{FG SHINE}____________________________________________________________________________@{FG TEXT}
ŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻŻ
    @{B}* Required@{UB}
      @{U}Short:@{UU}
       Write a short description of your program. (MAX 40 characters!)
       This will show up in the INDEX and RECENT so everyone can see
       what it is. Try to explain what your program does.
      @{U}Author:@{UU}
        The authors name and email. It's really important so people and
        Aminet workers can contact you!
      @{U}Uploader:@{UU}
        The uploaders name and email. Also really important for Aminet
        workers.
      @{U}Upload Type:@{UU}
        Where your program should be put on Aminet. This is only a guideline
        for those who works with Aminet, but you will make it easier for
        them with this!
      @{U}Distribution:@{UU}
        Ignore - Ignore this option.
        NoCDs  - Don't put the file on Aminet CDs.
        Aminet - The file will only be distributed on Aminet.
    @{B}* Additional@{UB}
      @{U}Kurz:@{UU}
        German version of Short.
      @{U}Replaces:@{UU}
        Let's you specify files that are superseded by this upload. It's
        very improtant to give full path.
        i.e biz/patch/PageStreamPatch*
      @{U}Required:@{UU}
        Other archives that your program needs to work, give full path.
        You can also specify OS, mem, chipset requirements here.
      @{U}Version:@{UU}
        Enter the version of your program.
    @{B}* Other@{UB}
      @{U}Edit description:@{UU}
        Launches c:ed and let's you write the long description of your
        program. When your done just save the file.
      @{U}Delete description:@{UU}
        Launces c:delete and deletes the description file.
      @{U}LHA Exe:@{UU}
        The path to lha and the executable.
      @{U}Archive:@{UU}
        The path and name to the archive that you want to be listed in
        the ReadMe.
      @{U}Write archive contents:@{UU}
        Select Yes if you want to write the archive contents and No if you
        don't.

    @{B}Output ReadMe:@{UB}
      The path and name of file where the readme should be created.
    @{B}Save ReadMe:@{UB}
      Starts making the readme!
    @{B}Input ReadMe:@{UB}
      The path and name of the ReadMe that should be loaded.
    @{B}Load ReadMe:@{UB}
      Loads the ReadMe.
    @{B}Save Prefs:@{UB}
      Saves the preferences to PROGDIR:CAR.prefs
    @{B}About:@{UB}
      Shows some info about the program.
    @{B}Quit:@{UB}
      Quits CreateAminetReadMe.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "History" "History"

 @{FG SHINE}@{U}History@{UU}:@{FG TEXT}

   @{B}0.1-0.9:@{UB} Internal beta versions.

   @{B}1.0:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1998-12-29) (11349 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · Fixed so all functions now work :)
   · Wrote the Guide.

   @{B}1.1:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1999-01-07) (13396 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · You can now load every ReadMe there is.

   @{B}1.2:@{UB} @{FG SHINE}(1999-01-09) (13659 bytes)@{FG TEXT}
   · I forgot the ASLFR_DoSaveMode for the load asl requester, it gave some
     trouble with MagicASL. I also fixed some patterns and titles for the ASL
     requesters.
   · I also forgot the ======= Archive Contents ======= line before the
     listing of the archive.
   · It was some minor trouble with Save Prefs if the Short field was empty.
   · It was some trouble with the load routine if the prefs file didn't
     exist.
@ENDNODE

